attributes.Long form description: The instructor tells him to exchange the battery, the student turns off the GoPro and then looks for the battery door, then exchanges the batteries. After that he exchanges the SD cards. The student turns on and off the Go pro. Then he has to place the Go pro into the strap, then into the tripod and at last changes the tripod for the handheld grip.

attributes.Transcription: Hello and thank you for agreeing to participate in our study.
You will see a GoPro action camera, we will be using it for this task.
First, please change the battery in the GoPro.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns off their GoPro.

attributes.Transcription: We will find the battery compartment on the right side of the GoPro.
To open it please slide down on the notch.
First, turn off the Gopro.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student turns on the GoPro.

attributes.Transcription: To open it please slide down the notch.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student can't open the battery door.

attributes.Transcription: You will see a small metal notch on the bottom of the right side.
On the right side, you will see a small hole in the metal.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student can't open the battery door.

attributes.Transcription: On the lower part at the ride side.
Please pull that downward.
Please put the battery at the base.
Please put in the battery.
Next, please change the micro sd card in the GoPro.

attributes.Action sentence: The student removes the SD card.

attributes.Transcription: Please put in the new micro SD card.

attributes.Action sentence: The student inserts a new SD card.

attributes.Transcription: Please click the door into place.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns on their Go pro.

attributes.Transcription: Next, please turn on the camera.
Please check the battery.
Turn, please stop the recording.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns off their Go pro.

attributes.Transcription: You turned on the camera, please use the button of the left.
Please wait to the camera finish turn on.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns on their Go pro.

attributes.Transcription: Please, turn off the camera.
Turn off the camera, please long press the button on the left.
Please now mount the shoulder strap to the Gopro.

attributes.Action sentence: The student mounts the strap onto the Gopro.

attributes.Transcription: To mount it first please unscrew the nut.
Please remove the screw from the Go pro and slide the GoPro into the mounting bracket.
Please slide the GoPro between. Please slide the GoPro between the brackets.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student can't insert the mount into the strap.

attributes.Action sentence: The student screws the Gopro lock.

attributes.Transcription: Make sure the Go pro is fully inserted.
Next, please change the mount on the GoPro from the shoulder strap to the tripod.

attributes.Action sentence: The student mounts the Go pro onto the tripod.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student can't insert the lock screw.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the lock screw on the tripod.

attributes.Transcription: Next, please change the mount from the tripod to the handheld mount.

attributes.Action sentence: The student mounts the handheld grip.

attributes.Transcription: Next please remove the mount from the Go pro.

attributes.Action sentence: The student removes their handheld grip.

attributes.Transcription: Thank you very much that will be everything for this task.
